# EEMS analysis

In this analysis, we will use EEMS to estimate the effective migration surface for *Ceratopipra rubrocapilla*. To run EEMS, we need a dataset of SNPs, a shapefile of the habitat/range of our species, and sampling coordinates for our samples.


# Format data
First, we need to format our input data. EEMS has the program bed2diff to convert data into the required eems input format. bed2diff takes input in plink binary format, which is a series of three files: bed, bim, and fam. We need to convert our SNP data into bed/bim/fam format.

plink can read VCF files, and it automatically converts the data to binary format. All we need to do is give plink our VCF and print the output.
